title: Minifier

The Aheadworks Minifier extension for Magento 2  is designed to speed up the page load by compressing images (changes the image weight only) by up to 70% (lossy compression), without reducing their quality. Since every second counts when your shop is loading as 40% of users abandon a website if it takes more than 3 seconds to load.



What’s more, Minifier is an efficient tool for improving your SEO value. Customizing image file names is absolutely crucial as they notify Google and other search engine crawlers as to the subject matter of the image. Minifier builds file names from a product type and product title. Both of them usually contain keywords.



All images compressed with Minifier belong to you and will not revert in case of uninstallation of the app.

title: Ultimate Site Maintenance
description:
Using this extension you can put Magento 2 sites into maintenance mode from the admin, and set a custom maintenance mode message as well. Instead of having to use FTP or SSH to put your Magento 2 sites into maintenance mode, you can use this extension to create a custom maintenance mode message, including using a WYSIWYG editor, set the timer to keep it in maintenance mode for different store views and also specify IP addresses those are allowed to access the frontend.

In the countdown timer, the time defined by the admin will not vary according to the time zone, so the site will be in maintenance mode at the same time all over world, regardless of the time zones. For example, if I set the time period 1 hour of maintenance mode as per IST times zone (Site server time) then the site will be in maintenance mode all over the world according to the IST time only. After this period, the site will automatically get live.

This extension is very easy to use. You just have to install i2t and enable it from admin and set the rest of the settings of the extensions as per need like IP addresses, custom maintenance message and countdown time etc. Using this extension, the site administrator can put the site in maintenance mode for a particular store.

Sometimes we need an extension to put the site in maintenance for some time period. Then this extension solves the problem related to maintenance. You can put the site in maintenance mode for a specified time like for 2 hours or 1 day. After your set time, the site will automatically go to normal state and maintenance mode will be disabled.

You can use this extension without setting any timer as well. In this case, you just need to enable it and set the message that you want to set for viewers through admin. You can put the particular store on the website in maintenance mode.

This extension whitelist IP addresses given in IP address field in admin so that you’re not locked out of the system.  So you’ll still be able to see the site on those IP addresses, but anyone else will see the custom maintenance message.

title: LayUp Digital Layby Solution
description: LayUp is an alternative payment platform that increases sales and basket size by enabling your customers to lay-by/layaway items with interest-free installment plans. With LayUp’s module, you can allow buyers to pay in installments for products or services that suit your business rules. Through the configuration settings, you simply define your business rules through two separate settings; the deposit down payment percentage and the final payment date as to when you want your customer to have paid up by. Our extension includes a payment widget, which will be enabled as a payment option in your checkout. Once a customer selects “Pay it off with LayUp” as their payment option, they are redirected to our secure checkout, after which they are taken back to your store to view their purchase details. The extension also includes a widget that displays a dynamic installment amount on your product and cart pages, which is proven to increase conversions and basket size. Once your customer has chosen the “Pay it off with LayUp” payment option, they will be directed to a customized payment widget page where they are able to toggle between weekly or monthly installments. They can also select the day of the week or month they will like to be billed on throughout the payment plan period as well as their being total transparency and clarity of what the future installments are going to be. When your customer is ready to activate their payment plan, they can choose between paying via credit/ debit card or instant EFT. After the customer has successfully gone through 3D secure process and verified themselves they will be redirected back to your store to view their purchase details and the order will be put into a “placed” state. If the customer is declined for whatever reason, the item will be put back in-stock to be sold in the future.
